+project: spatial-nav
+title: 'Nav bar (LeftNav): reachable from every view via left-edge nav'
+---
+## What
+
+The LeftNav view-switcher strip sits on the left edge of the window. The user expects universal spatial nav: from anywhere in the window layer, pressing `h` enough times eventually lands on a LeftNav button. No view should trap focus.
+
+Today, LeftNav renders plain `<button>` elements with no FocusScope — it's invisible to spatial nav. Also, `h` at the leftmost column of a grid / board stays put (soft clamp) instead of crossing the boundary into LeftNav.
+
+This task is the GENERIC version — ensure LeftNav is reachable from the board, the grid, and any future view that lives in the window layer. Inspector is excluded by design (it's a layer above the window; nav is trapped).
+
+### TDD — failing tests (one per view)
+
+Under `kanban-app/e2e/spatial-nav-leftnav.e2e.ts`:
+
+```ts
+describe("LeftNav reachable from all views", () => {
+  it("h from leftmost card in a board column moves focus to the active LeftNav button", async () => {
+    await openBoardFixture();
+    await click(cardEl("card-1-1"));
+    await keyboard("h"); // at leftmost column already
+    const focused = await getFocusedMoniker();
+    expect(focused).toMatch(/^view:/);
+  });
+
+  it("h from the row selector in a grid moves focus to the active LeftNav button", async () => {
+    await openTagsGridFixture();
+    await click(rowSelectorEl(0));
+    await keyboard("h");
+    const focused = await getFocusedMoniker();
+    expect(focused).toMatch(/^view:/);
+  });
+
+  it("j/k between LeftNav view buttons", async () => {
+    await click(viewButtonEl("board"));
+    await keyboard("j");
+    const focused = await getFocusedMoniker();
+    expect(focused).toMatch(/^view:/);
+    expect(focused).not.toBe("view:board");
+  });
+
+  it("l from an active LeftNav button moves into the active view", async () => {
+    await click(viewButtonEl("board"));
+    await keyboard("l");
+    const focused = await getFocusedMoniker();
+    expect(focused).toMatch(/^(task:|tag:|field:)/);
+  });
+});
+```
+
+### Approach
+
+1. Wrap each view button in `LeftNav` in a `FocusScope` with `moniker("view", view.id)`.
+2. Because the button is the DOM element (not a div), use `renderContainer={false}` and wire the element ref via a context pattern — e.g. `FocusScopeElementRefContext` (depends on the generalization of this ref-sharing pattern; may live in the cell-nav task first).
+3. Show focus bar: false (LeftNav has its own active-state styling).
+
+### Acceptance
+
+- [ ] All 4 E2E tests pass
+- [ ] Clicking a LeftNav button still dispatches `view.switch:<id>`
+- [ ] Tooltip still shows on hover
+- [ ] No regression in any other nav test
\ No newline at end of file

